author: mel@gmail.com
content: Actually it is easier to play in F. His voice sat in a nice place in F at the time. He also wasnt touring the world when he did the recordings. I know several musicians that played w/ him and theyve always done it in E. Not sure why youre bugged about me playing it in a different E. Keith Emerson changed keys on many of his compositions for Greg Lakes voice. Sometimes as much as a 3rd or 4th. Its all about playing a song where the singers voice sits comfortably.
